  "articleSummary": "This article argues that practical developer workstation security lies between useless enterprise advice and extreme survivalist measures, focusing on reducing the \"blast radius\" when code runs as the user. It recommends four defense layers: isolation via Dev Containers with narrow mounts (avoiding mounts of `~/.ssh`, cloud configs, etc.), replacing plaintext `.env` files with encrypted secret management (using tools like VarLock), planting canary tokens for detection, and controlling egress. The tone is a pragmatic, instructional guide for developers and tech leads, using metaphors like \"typing through wet cement\" and \"digital attic\" to frame the approach.",
